\title{Devcontainer Setup}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Creates devcontainers with Claude Code, language-specific tooling (Python/Node/Rust/Go), and persistent volumes. Use when adding devcontainer support to a project, setting up isolated development environments, or configuring sandboxed Claude Code workspaces.}

\subtree{
\title{Devcontainer Setup Skill}
\p{Creates a pre-configured devcontainer with Claude Code and language-specific tooling.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{User asks to "set up a devcontainer" or "add devcontainer support"}
\li{User wants a sandboxed Claude Code development environment}
\li{User needs isolated development environments with persistent configuration}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\ul{
\li{User already has a devcontainer configuration and just needs modifications}
\li{User is asking about general Docker or container questions}
\li{User wants to deploy production containers (this is for development only)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\pre{\startverb
flowchart TB
    start([User requests devcontainer])
    recon[1. Project Reconnaissance]
    detect[2. Detect Languages]
    generate[3. Generate Configuration]
    write[4. Write files to .devcontainer/]
    done([Done])

    start --> recon
    recon --> detect
    detect --> generate
    generate --> write
    write --> done
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 1: Project Reconnaissance}
\subtree{
\title{Infer Project Name}
\p{Check in order (use first match):}

\ol{
\li{\code{\startverb package.json\stopverb} → \code{\startverb name\stopverb} field}
\li{\code{\startverb pyproject.toml\stopverb} → \code{\startverb project.name\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb Cargo.toml\stopverb} → \code{\startverb package.name\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb go.mod\stopverb} → module path (last segment after \code{\startverb /\stopverb})}
\li{Directory name as fallback}
}

\p{Convert to slug: lowercase, replace spaces/underscores with hyphens.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Detect Language Stack}
\pre{\startverb
| Language | Detection Files |
|----------|-----------------|
| Python | `pyproject.toml`, `*.py` |
| Node/TypeScript | `package.json`, `tsconfig.json` |
| Rust | `Cargo.toml` |
| Go | `go.mod`, `go.sum` |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Multi-Language Projects}
\p{If multiple languages are detected, configure all of them in the following priority order:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Python} - Primary language, uses Dockerfile for uv + Python installation}
\li{\strong{Node/TypeScript} - Uses devcontainer feature}
\li{\strong{Rust} - Uses devcontainer feature}
\li{\strong{Go} - Uses devcontainer feature}
}

\p{For multi-language \code{\startverb postCreateCommand\stopverb}, chain all setup commands:}

\pre{\startverb
uv run /opt/post_install.py && uv sync && npm ci
\stopverb}

\p{Extensions and settings from all detected languages should be merged into the configuration.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Phase 2: Generate Configuration}
\p{Start with base templates from \code{\startverb resources/\stopverb} directory. Substitute:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb {{PROJECT_NAME}}\stopverb} → Human-readable name (e.g., "My Project")}
\li{\code{\startverb {{PROJECT_SLUG}}\stopverb} → Slug for volumes (e.g., "my-project")}
}

\p{Then apply language-specific modifications below.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Base Template Features}
\p{The base template includes:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Claude Code} with marketplace plugins (anthropics/skills, trailofbits/skills, trailofbits/skills-curated)}
\li{\strong{Python 3.13} via uv (fast binary download)}
\li{\strong{Node 22} via fnm (Fast Node Manager)}
\li{\strong{ast-grep} for AST-based code search}
\li{\strong{Network isolation tools} (iptables, ipset) with NET_ADMIN capability}
\li{\strong{Modern CLI tools}: ripgrep, fd, fzf, tmux, git-delta}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Language-Specific Sections}
\subtree{
\title{Python Projects}
\p{\strong{Detection:} \code{\startverb pyproject.toml\stopverb}, \code{\startverb requirements.txt\stopverb}, \code{\startverb setup.py\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb *.py\stopverb} files}

\p{\strong{Dockerfile additions:}}

\p{The base Dockerfile already includes Python 3.13 via uv. If a different version is required (detected from \code{\startverb pyproject.toml\stopverb}), modify the Python installation:}

\pre{\startverb
# Install Python via uv (fast binary download, not source compilation)
RUN uv python install <version> --default
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{devcontainer.json extensions:}}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.extensions\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"ms-python.python",
"ms-python.vscode-pylance",
"charliermarsh.ruff"
\stopverb}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.settings\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"python.defaultInterpreterPath": ".venv/bin/python",
"[python]": {
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "charliermarsh.ruff",
  "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
    "source.organizeImports": "explicit"
  }
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{postCreateCommand:} If \code{\startverb pyproject.toml\stopverb} exists, chain commands:}

\pre{\startverb
rm -rf .venv && uv sync && uv run /opt/post_install.py
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Node/TypeScript Projects}
\p{\strong{Detection:} \code{\startverb package.json\stopverb} or \code{\startverb tsconfig.json\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{No Dockerfile additions needed:} The base template includes Node 22 via fnm (Fast Node Manager).}

\p{\strong{devcontainer.json extensions:}}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.extensions\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"dbaeumer.vscode-eslint",
"esbenp.prettier-vscode"
\stopverb}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.settings\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"editor.defaultFormatter": "esbenp.prettier-vscode",
"editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
  "source.fixAll.eslint": "explicit"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{postCreateCommand:} Detect package manager from lockfile and chain with base command:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb pnpm-lock.yaml\stopverb} → \code{\startverb uv run /opt/post_install.py && pnpm install --frozen-lockfile\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb yarn.lock\stopverb} → \code{\startverb uv run /opt/post_install.py && yarn install --frozen-lockfile\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb package-lock.json\stopverb} → \code{\startverb uv run /opt/post_install.py && npm ci\stopverb}}
\li{No lockfile → \code{\startverb uv run /opt/post_install.py && npm install\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rust Projects}
\p{\strong{Detection:} \code{\startverb Cargo.toml\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Features to add:}}

\pre{\startverb
"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/rust:1": {}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{devcontainer.json extensions:}}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.extensions\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"rust-lang.rust-analyzer",
"tamasfe.even-better-toml"
\stopverb}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.settings\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"[rust]": {
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "rust-lang.rust-analyzer"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{postCreateCommand:} If \code{\startverb Cargo.lock\stopverb} exists, use locked builds:}

\pre{\startverb
uv run /opt/post_install.py && cargo build --locked
\stopverb}

\p{If no lockfile, use standard build:}

\pre{\startverb
uv run /opt/post_install.py && cargo build
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Go Projects}
\p{\strong{Detection:} \code{\startverb go.mod\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Features to add:}}

\pre{\startverb
"ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/go:1": {
  "version": "latest"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{devcontainer.json extensions:}}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.extensions\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"golang.go"
\stopverb}

\p{Add to \code{\startverb customizations.vscode.settings\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"[go]": {
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "golang.go"
},
"go.useLanguageServer": true
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{postCreateCommand:}}

\pre{\startverb
uv run /opt/post_install.py && go mod download
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Reference Material}
\p{For additional guidance, see:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb references/dockerfile-best-practices.md\stopverb} - Layer optimization, multi-stage builds, architecture support}
\li{\code{\startverb references/features-vs-dockerfile.md\stopverb} - When to use devcontainer features vs custom Dockerfile}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Adding Persistent Volumes}
\p{Pattern for new mounts in \code{\startverb devcontainer.json\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
"mounts": [
  "source={{PROJECT_SLUG}}-<purpose>-${devcontainerId},target=<container-path>,type=volume"
]
\stopverb}

\p{Common additions:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb source={{PROJECT_SLUG}}-cargo-${devcontainerId},target=/home/vscode/.cargo,type=volume\stopverb} (Rust)}
\li{\code{\startverb source={{PROJECT_SLUG}}-go-${devcontainerId},target=/home/vscode/go,type=volume\stopverb} (Go)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output Files}
\p{Generate these files in the project's \code{\startverb .devcontainer/\stopverb} directory:}

\ol{
\li{\code{\startverb Dockerfile\stopverb} - Container build instructions}
\li{\code{\startverb devcontainer.json\stopverb} - VS Code/devcontainer configuration}
\li{\code{\startverb post_install.py\stopverb} - Post-creation setup script}
\li{\code{\startverb .zshrc\stopverb} - Shell configuration}
\li{\code{\startverb install.sh\stopverb} - CLI helper for managing the devcontainer (\code{\startverb devc\stopverb} command)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Validation Checklist}
\p{Before presenting files to the user, verify:}

\ol{
\li{All \code{\startverb {{PROJECT_NAME}}\stopverb} placeholders are replaced with the human-readable name}
\li{All \code{\startverb {{PROJECT_SLUG}}\stopverb} placeholders are replaced with the slugified name}
\li{JSON syntax is valid in \code{\startverb devcontainer.json\stopverb} (no trailing commas, proper nesting)}
\li{Language-specific extensions are added for all detected languages}
\li{\code{\startverb postCreateCommand\stopverb} includes all required setup commands (chained with \code{\startverb &&\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{User Instructions}
\p{After generating, inform the user:}

\ol{
\li{How to start: "Open in VS Code and select 'Reopen in Container'"}
\li{Alternative: \code{\startverb devcontainer up --workspace-folder .\stopverb}}
\li{CLI helper: Run \code{\startverb .devcontainer/install.sh self-install\stopverb} to add the \code{\startverb devc\stopverb} command to PATH}
}
}
}